tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE OutreachMetrics (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name STRING,
    response_rate FLOAT,
    conversion_rate FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE outreach_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_id INT,
    response_date DATE,
    responses_received INT,
    conversions INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (strategy_id) REFERENCES outreach_strategies(strategy_id)
);

CREATE TABLE outreach_strategies (
   strategy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   strategy_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
   start_date DATE,
   end_date DATE,
   response_rate DECIMAL(5,2),
   conversion_rate DECIMAL(5,2)
);

CREATE TABLE audience_feedback (
   feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   strategy_id INT,
   feedback_text TEXT,
   feedback_date DATE,
   FOREIGN KEY (strategy_id) REFERENCES outreach_strategies(strategy_id)
);

CREATE TABLE campaign_metrics (
   metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   strategy_id INT,
   campaign_date DATE,
   impressions INT,
   clicks INT,
   conversions INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (strategy_id) REFERENCES outreach_strategies(strategy_id)
);

CREATE TABLE performance_tracking (
   tracking_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   strategy_id INT,
   tracking_date DATE,
   response_status BOOLEAN,
   conversion_status BOOLEAN,
   FOREIGN KEY (strategy_id) REFERENCES outreach_strategies(strategy_id)
);
CREATE TABLE outreach_strategies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, strategy_name VARCHAR(255), response_rate FLOAT, conversion_rate FLOAT);
CREATE TABLE emails_sent (id INT PRIMARY KEY, strategy_id INT, email_address VARCHAR(255), sent_date TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE responses_received (id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(50), response_date TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE conversions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, response_id INT, conversion_type VARCHAR(50), conversion_date TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE campaign_results (id INT PRIMARY KEY, strategy_id INT, success BOOLEAN, result_date DATE);
